<br>
What this means is that if we hold the lightbulb size at 3 meters by 1 meter, with 10 square meters of surface, passing 30,000 Megawatts, then each square meter would have to be cooled of a &quot;mere&quot; 6 megawatts of absorbed energy per centimeter of thickness of the bulb.<br>
<br>
